            <p><b>Andhra Pradesh</b> is a state in the southern coastal region of India. It is the seventh-largest state with an area of 162,970 kmÂ² and the tenth-most populous state with 49,577,103 inhabitants. It has shared borders with Telangana, Chhattisgarh, Odisha, Tamil Nadu, Karnataka, and the Bay of Bengal.Charminar, Hyderabad:

               <b> Charminar is an iconic monument located in the heart of Hyderabad.</b>
                Visitors can explore the historic structure and even climb to the top for panoramic views of the city.
                Entry Fee: Approximately INR 25 for Indian tourists and INR 300 for foreign tourists.
                Timing: 9:30 AM to 5:30 PM (Closed on Fridays).
                Tirupati Balaji Temple,
                <br>
                <br> <b>Tirumala:  <br>              
                Tirupati Balaji Temple is a renowned Hindu pilgrimage site located in the Tirumala Hills.</b>
                Devotees visit to seek the blessings of Lord Venkateswara.
                Special Darshan: Approximate cost ranges from INR 300 to INR 500 per person.
                Laddu Prasadam: Additional charges apply.
                <br>
                <br><b>
                Araku Valley:<br>
                Araku Valley is a picturesque hill station in Andhra Pradesh, known for its lush green landscapes and coffee plantations.</b>
                Visitors can enjoy scenic train rides and explore tribal culture.
                Train Ticket (Vistadome Coach): Approximately INR 600 to INR 1000 per person.
                <br>
                <br><b>Borra Caves:
               
                <br>
                Borra Caves are natural limestone formations located in the Ananthagiri Hills.</b>
                The caves feature stunning stalactites and stalagmites.
                Entry Fee: Approximately INR 40 for adults and INR 30 for children.
                <br>
                <br><b>Vizag Beaches (Rushikonda and Rama Krishna Beach):
                
                <br>
                Vizag boasts beautiful beaches like Rushikonda and Rama Krishna Beach.</b>
                Visitors can relax, enjoy water sports, and savor local seafood.
                Water Sports: Prices vary based on activities.
                <br>
                <br><b>Sri Venkateswara Zoological Park, Tirupati:
                
                <br>
                 zoological park is home to a wide variety of animals and birds.</b>
                Visitors can explore the park's lush greenery and wildlife.
                Entry Fee: Approximately INR 30 for adults and INR 15 for children.
                <br>
                <br><b></b>Kailasagiri, Visakhapatnam:
                <br>
                
                 is a hilltop park offering panoramic views of Visakhapatnam.</b>
                Visitors can enjoy the ropeway ride and explore the park.
                Ropeway Ride: Approximately INR 100 for adults and INR 50 for children.
                Please note that these are approximate price ranges and may vary based on factors such as nationality, age, and special packages. It's advisable to check the official websites or contact the respective attractions for the most up-to-date pricing information before planning your visit.</p>
